  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance on Shelter and Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) for Super Typhoon Rai Affected People</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM&#x2019;s response to Typhoon Rai (Odette) aims to mitigate the impact of the typhoon on the most vulnerable populations, which has multi-sectoral approaches to address their outstanding needs of shelter, water, sanitation and hygiene, and mental health and psychosocial support. Target communities include the most vulnerable and hard-to-reach communities in Southern Leyte in Eastern Visayas Region and as well as in Dinagat Islands, and Surigao del Norte (including Siargao Island) in Caraga Region.</narrative>
  </description>
